    "Id": "vehiclechassisdef_SCHREK_AC",
    "Name": "Schrek (AC)",
    "Details": "<b>Name: <color=#85DBF6>Schrek AC Carrier</color>\nArmor: <color=#85DBF6>Standard </color>\tTechnology: <color=#85DBF6>Inner Sphere</color>\nMovement: <color=#85DBF6>4/7 (Tracked)</color>\tEngine: <color=#85DBF6>240 ICE</color></b>\n\nThe Schrek PPC carrier, designed for long-range bombardments, is capable of unleashing a deadly rain of particle fire.\n\nThis Schrek, repurposed as an \"autocannon carrier\", was born of the dark days of the Third Succession War, when Schreks were often cannibalized to replace the PPCs or fusion engines of BattleMechs. Three AC/5s with three tons of ammunition and eight Machine Guns replaced the energy weapons. Stripping out unneeded heat sinks also allowed extra armor to be added.",
